# Transaction ETL Dashboard Summary

This dashboard was created using Power BI to analyze transaction and fraud data after completing the ETL process using Python and SQL Server.

The dashboard provides insights into:

* Total transactions
* Total revenue
* Fraud activity
* Transaction trends
* Device usage
* Payment methods

The visualizations help identify fraud patterns, customer behavior, and business performance.

## Dashboard Visuals

* KPI Cards for total revenue, transactions, and fraud count
* Bar Charts for transaction types and device usage
* Donut Charts for fraud vs non-fraud transactions
* Line Charts for transaction trends over time
* Revenue analysis by network slice and region

## Technologies Used

* Python
* SQL Server
* Power BI
* Pandas
* SQLAlchemy

## Project Outcome

This project demonstrates an end-to-end ETL and business intelligence workflow that converts raw transaction data into interactive dashboards and business insights.

